SCOPE — code vs. health content
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The MIT licence above covers the SOURCE CODE of this project only.

It does NOT relicense the third-party health information bundled with the app
(the Retrieval-Augmented Generation corpus under `lib/server/rag/sources/` and
the curated knowledge base). That material remains under the licences of its
original publishers, several of which are NON-COMMERCIAL and SHARE-ALIKE:

  - World Health Organization (WHO)  — CC BY-NC-SA 3.0 IGO
  - NHS England                      — Open Government Licence v3.0
  - Govt. of Bangladesh (DGHS/DGFP)  — public information, used with attribution
  - icddr,b                          — © icddr,b, cite the source

Each source document records its own licence in its `.md` frontmatter, and full
attribution and required disclaimers are in ATTRIBUTION.md. If you reuse this
project, you must keep that attribution and honour those content licences —
notably, the WHO-derived material may not be used commercially.

Shokhi provides general health information, not a diagnosis.
